==English==
=== Etymology ===
Old English. Cognate with '[[green]]'' and ''[[grass]]''. Akin to Old High German ''[[gruowan]]'' (to grow), probably Korean [[기르다]] [gireuda] (to grow) and [[길이]] [giri] (length), and Breton ''[[hir]]'' [as of [[menhir]]] (long).

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /gr@U/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ɡrəʊ/

===Verb===
{{irregverb|'''to grow'''|'''[[grows]]'''|'''[[grew]]'''|'''[[grown]]'''|'''[[growing]]'''}}

#''(intransitive)'' To [[become]] [[bigger]].
#''(intransitive)'' To [[appear]] or [[sprout]].
#:''The plant began to '''grow'''
#:''A long tail began to '''grow''' from his backside.''
#''(transitive)'' To cause something to become bigger, especially plants.

